A comparison of complex code versus clean, readable code:

```cpp
// DIRTY CODE: Large function doing too many operations
void Process(float dt) {
    // Check state, loop through nodes, update positions, render meshes, play sounds...
}

// CLEAN CODE: Small, single-responsibility helper functions
void UpdateGameplayTick(float DeltaTime) {
    UpdatePlayerPositions(DeltaTime);
    UpdateAIVisionChecks();
    PruneExpiredParticles();
}
```
